    "The comprehensive interpretation of LLM vulnerabilities under XAI, including backdoor attacks, membership inference attacks (MIA), and model extraction attacks, has yet to be fully explored.",
    "Additionally, vulnerabilities related to prompt injection and jailbreaking attacks in the context of XAI still remain unexplored.",
    "Furthermore, open-sourced LLMs are publicly accessible and may provide greater explainability than closed-source models.",
    "However, this enhanced accessibility can make them more vulnerable to attacks when XAI techniques are employed.",
    "Thus, these LLMs may be more susceptible to attacks due to XAI."
